How to call it (drop‑in snippets)

Assume you already have:

final BlobContainerClient ERRORS_CONTAINER =
    BlobClientProvider.container(System.getenv("Blob_ContainerName_Errors"));
final String functionName = "NeoCosmosChangeFeedTrigger";
final String invocationId = context.getInvocationId();



1) Bad JSON (parse failure → no newDoc)

catch (com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException jpe) {
    ErrorWriter.writeError(
        ERRORS_CONTAINER,
        cosmosContainerName,
        /*docId*/ null,
        "DataError.BadJson",
        jpe.getOriginalMessage(),
        "UNKNOWN",
        /*newDoc*/ null,     // we couldn't parse it
        /*etagAtRead*/ null,
        invocationId,
        functionName,
        log
    );
    // skip this item; continue with the rest
}

2) Missing id (parsed but no id)

if (docId == null || docId.isBlank()) {
    ErrorWriter.writeError(
        ERRORS_CONTAINER,
        cosmosContainerName,
        null,
        "DataError.MissingId",
        "Change feed item missing 'id'.",
        "UNKNOWN",
        newDoc,          // include the parsed doc so you can inspect it later
        null,
        invocationId,
        functionName,
        log
    );
    continue;
}

3) Service Bus send failed (transient infra; you will rethrow to retry)

try {
    // busSender.sendMessage(msg);
} catch (Exception sbEx) {
    ErrorWriter.writeError(
        ERRORS_CONTAINER,
        cosmosContainerName,
        docId,
        "Infra.ServiceBusSendFail",
        sbEx.getMessage(),
        isCreate ? "CREATE" : "MODIFY",
        newDoc,
        current.eTag(),                   // if you read a baseline, pass its ETag; else null
        invocationId,
        functionName,
        log
    );
    throw sbEx; // let Functions retry the whole batch
}

4) Blob snapshot write failed (transient infra; rethrow to retry)

try {
    if (isCreate) {
        CreateBlob.createBlobIfCreateEvent(DATA_CONTAINER, cosmosContainerName, docId, newDoc, log);
    } else {
        UpdateBlob.overwriteWithVersioning(DATA_CONTAINER, cosmosContainerName, docId, newDoc, current.eTag(), log);
    }
} catch (RuntimeException storageEx) {
    ErrorWriter.writeError(
        ERRORS_CONTAINER,
        cosmosContainerName,
        docId,
        "Infra.BlobWriteFail",
        storageEx.getMessage(),
        isCreate ? "CREATE" : "MODIFY",
        newDoc,
        current.eTag(),
        invocationId,
        functionName,
        log
    );
    throw storageEx; // retry invocation
}

5) Rule evaluation failure (data/config issue; don’t kill the batch)

try {
    boolean shouldNotify = BusinessRules.evaluate(cosmosContainerName, newDoc);
    // ...
} catch (Exception rulesEx) {
    ErrorWriter.writeError(
        ERRORS_CONTAINER,
        cosmosContainerName,
        docId,
        "Rules.EvaluationError",
        rulesEx.getMessage(),
        isCreate ? "CREATE" : "MODIFY",
        newDoc,
        current.eTag(),
        invocationId,
        functionName,
        log
    );
    // continue (don’t throw) so lease advances
}


